# Role List Search Flow (By Name):

01. RoleListView.jsp me search field banayi gayi:
    <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Enter Role Name">

02. User name enter karta hai aur Search button par click karta hai.

03. Form submit hota hai aur request RoleListCtl ke doPost() method me jati hai.

04. doPost() method me:
    - pageNo aur pageSize request se liye jate hain
    - operation parameter nikala jata hai

05. Check kiya jata hai:
    if (OP_SEARCH.equalsIgnoreCase(op))

06. OP_SEARCH hone par:
    pageNo = 1 set kiya jata hai (search hamesha first page se start hota hai)

07. populateBean(request) call hota hai:
    - RoleBean me name set hota hai (search value)

08. RoleModel ka object banaya jata hai:
    RoleModel model = new RoleModel();

09. model.search(bean, pageNo, pageSize) call hota hai.

10. RoleModel.search() method me SQL query banti hai:
    select * from st_role where 1=1

11. Agar bean.getName() empty nahi hai:
    SQL me condition add hoti hai:
    and name like 'searchValue%'

12. Query execute hoti hai aur matching records database se fetch hote hain.

13. Retrieved list controller me aati hai.

14. Agar list empty hoti hai:
    ServletUtility.setErrorMessage("No record found", request) set hota hai.

15. Data request me set kiya jata hai:
    - setList(list)
    - setPageNo(pageNo)
    - setPageSize(pageSize)
    - setBean(bean)

16. next page check ke liye:
    model.search(bean, pageNo + 1, pageSize) call hota hai
    aur nextListSize set kiya jata hai

17. ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hota hai.

18. Request wapas RoleListView.jsp par forward hoti hai.

19. JSP par:
    - list ko iterate karke sirf matching records display kiye jate hain
